## Worked Examples

### ESF Balance Sheet (Single Lookup)
**Q:** "Total nominal capital held as per ESF as of March 31, 1989?"
```
grep -n "Total capital" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1989_*.txt /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1990_*.txt
→ Read 10 lines above each match to find table with "March 31, 1989" column
→ Extract "Total capital" = 8124453 (thousands) → 8.124 billion
```
**Answer:** `8.124`

### T-Bill Rate (Date Answer)
**Q:** "When did the 91-day T-bill rate first exceed 10% in 1981?"
```
grep -n "91-day\|Discount Rate\|Weekly Bill" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1981_*.txt
→ Read matched sections, scan chronologically for first rate > 10.00
```
**Answer:** `March 3, 1981`

### Multi-Year Mean (MCP Tool)
**Q:** "Mean gross federal debt for FY 2015-2020?"
```bash
for y in 2015 2016 2017 2018 2019 2020; do
  echo "=== FY$y ==="; grep -n "Gross Federal Debt" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_${y}_12.txt | head -5
done
```
Then: `mcpcalc calculate(calculator: "mean", inputs: {values: [...]})` or `sum(values)/len(values)`

### Annualized Volatility (Statistical Calculation)
**Q:** "Annualized realized volatility of monthly 91-day T-bill rates for 2010-2015?"
```bash
for y in 2010 2011 2012 2013 2014 2015; do
  for m in 03 06 09 12; do
    f="/app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_${y}_${m}.txt"
    [ -f "$f" ] && echo "=== ${y}_${m} ===" && grep -n "91-day" "$f" | head -3
  done
done
```
Compute: `std(returns) × √12` via mcpcalc or Python.

### Pre-1940s Lookup
**Q:** "Total federal expenditures in FY 1938?"
```
grep -i "expenditure\|disbursement\|total.*outlay" /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1938_*.txt /app/corpus/treasury_bulletin_1939_*.txt
→ Check units carefully — older docs may not use "thousands" convention
